.DT
add_position
Disk World creator help
add_position

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
add_position -  Dummy function for guilds without positions This method adds a new position for the subguild.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int add_position(string sub_guild,
string position,
int max,
string * abilities,
mixed * description)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^sub_guild%^RESET%^ - the sub guild
%^BOLD%^position%^RESET%^ - position to add
%^BOLD%^max%^RESET%^ - the maximum number of people appointed to this position
%^BOLD%^abilities%^RESET%^ - the abilities associated with this position
%^BOLD%^description%^RESET%^ - the descriptions associated with this position
({ title|({male_title,female_title}), ... })
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
DEITY_POSITION_OK if successful, DEITY_POSITION_FAIL if the
position already exists.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/guilds/standard.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

Dummy function for guilds without positions
This method adds a new position for the subguild.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
remove_position(), query_position(), query_positions()

.EP

